import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='wheat', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of wheat production over the years?', wrap=True)
    return chart

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='wages', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['wages'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['wages'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wages?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='year', y='wheat', data=data, color='blue')
    chart.axhline(y=data['wheat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['wheat'].mean():.2f}")
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title('What is the average wheat production?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
